  "body": "\r\n### Description\r\nI am running a private blockchain on Kubernetes, following the official setup guides with no real customisation to the genesis file. \r\n\r\nDuring an update of my kubernetes cluster, unfortunately all pods were stopped causing a full resync. (See Screenshots)\r\n\r\nNo data was lost as they were stored on persistent volumes, however now when the pods are syncing there is an interval of 5 seconds. Because the blockchain was running for some time, this will take weeks or months to complete the sync. \r\n\r\n![Screenshot 2023-03-29 at 12 52 40](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/50111269/228527425-810d4b03-0a81-4706-b1bf-7f5cb1e780cf.png)\r\n\r\nIs there anyway for me to continue mining blocks without needing to sync them between all nodes? \r\n\r\nI have tried to change the sync mode but I cannot seem to do this on a private network. \r\n\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:**\r\n\r\nBlocks quickly resync and blockchain is restarted\r\n\r\n**Actual behavior:**\r\n\r\nBlocks are syncing correctly, but one is only processed every 5 seconds. \r\n\r\n\r\n**Pod Startup** \r\n\r\n![Screenshot 2023-03-29 at 12 53 11](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/50111269/228527420-0654da46-166e-473f-948e-8dc35828f870.png)\r\n![Screenshot 2023-03-29 at 12 53 16](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/50111269/228527410-7b97d605-13de-403d-8a81-3370ad3dcce2.png)\r\n\r\n",
